<PARAGRAPH>
The 3C’s model points out that a strategist should focus on three key factors for success. In the construction of a business strategy, three main players must be taken into account:
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
A.	The Corporation
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
B.	The Customer
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
C.	The Competitors
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
Only by integrating these three C’s (Corporation, Customer, Competitors) in a strategic triangle, a sustained competitive advantage can exist. 
